log:
Generate an Apache Wayang plan that computes, for each nation and each order year, the total profit for all parts whose p_name contains the substring "green". Use the following tables and joins (exact join keys):

- part join lineitem on part.p_partkey = lineitem.l_partkey
- supplier join lineitem on supplier.s_suppkey = lineitem.l_suppkey
- partsupp join part and supplier on partsupp.ps_partkey = part.p_partkey AND partsupp.ps_suppkey = supplier.s_suppkey
- lineitem join orders on lineitem.l_orderkey = orders.o_orderkey
- supplier join nation on supplier.s_nationkey = nation.n_nationkey

For each joined lineitem row, extract the order year from orders.o_orderdate. Filter parts so that p_name contains the substring "green". Compute profit per row as:

profit = (l_extendedprice * (1 - l_discount)) - (ps_supplycost * l_quantity)

Group the filtered rows by nation.n_name and order year, and compute total_profit = SUM(profit) for each (nation, year) group. Output the final results (nation, year, total_profit) to a text file.

log.thoughts: The query explicitly requires joining part, supplier, lineitem, partsupp, orders, and nation tables, filtering parts where p_name contains 'green', extracting the order year from orders, computing profit using l_extendedprice, l_discount, ps_supplycost, and l_quantity, grouping by nation and year, and writing output to a text file. I included a target output text file 'result.txt' to store the plan results.

steps.detailed_description: Load all required input tables from JDBC: part (all columns), lineitem (all columns), supplier (all columns), partsupp (all columns), orders (all columns), and nation (all columns). These inputs will be the source datasets for subsequent joins and transformations.

Perform the necessary joins to produce one combined relational stream of line items enriched with part, supplier, partsupp, orders, and nation information. Use the exact join keys: part JOIN lineitem ON part.p_partkey = lineitem.l_partkey; supplier JOIN lineitem ON supplier.s_suppkey = lineitem.l_suppkey; partsupp JOIN part AND supplier ON partsupp.ps_partkey = part.p_partkey AND partsupp.ps_suppkey = supplier.s_suppkey; lineitem JOIN orders ON lineitem.l_orderkey = orders.o_orderkey; supplier JOIN nation ON supplier.s_nationkey = nation.n_nationkey. Output rows must include at least: nation.n_name, orders.o_orderdate, part.p_name, lineitem.l_extendedprice, lineitem.l_discount, partsupp.ps_supplycost, lineitem.l_quantity.

On the joined dataset: 1) Filter rows where part.p_name contains the substring 'green' (case-sensitive per dataset values). 2) Extract order year from orders.o_orderdate (produce an integer year column). 3) For each row compute profit = (l_extendedprice * (1 - l_discount)) - (ps_supplycost * l_quantity) and append as a numeric column. 4) Group the filtered rows by nation.n_name and the extracted order year, and compute total_profit = SUM(profit) per (nation, year) group. The output of this step is aggregated rows with columns: n_name, order_year, total_profit.

Write the aggregated results to a text file. Output columns (in each output row) must be: nation (n_name), year (order_year), total_profit. Use a plain text output (one record per line, fields delimited as required by downstream) to the requested text file destination.
